# Git commits: user only (katharina-brenner)

**The agent must NEVER run `git commit`, `git commit --amend`, or create commits on behalf of the user.**

All commits are made manually by **katharina-brenner** in the terminal or Git UI.

## Agent behavior

- Do **not** commit changes, even when the user says "save to git" or "publish" — instead prepare changes and give clear `git add` / `git commit` instructions for the user.
- Do **not** push unless the user explicitly asks to push in that message.
- After code changes, summarize what changed and which files the user should stage — do not commit for them.
- If the user asks to "commit", respond with the exact commands they should run locally (so authorship stays under their Git identity).

## User identity

Commits on this repo should appear as **katharina-brenner** on GitHub, not as Cursor Agent or any automated author.

The user configures their identity locally (agent does not change `git config`):

```powershell
git config --local user.name "katharina-brenner"
git config --local user.email "<your-github-email>"
```
